result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica Lee Ross was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-False Representation >$10,000-$100,000, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(d).
  • Forgery-Uttering, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(2).
  • Identity Theft - Obtain Money or Credit [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.203(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Must report to Probation. All amounts to be paid to Clerk of Court's office during probation term but as a condition of probation.

miscConds.notes: $290.60 fine/costs to be paid to the Clerk of Court's Office within 60 days or set up payment plan. Failure to pay may result in a tax intercept, license suspension, warrant and/or civil judgment subject to collection efforts.

$250.00 DNA surcharge to be paid to the Clerk of Court's Office within 60 days or set up payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in a tax intercept, license suspension, warrant and/or civil judgment subject to collection efforts.
May not possess or use firearms and, if considered a violent felony, no body armor.
Must complete an AODA assessment and comply with recommendations.

Absolute Sobriety. 
No use or possession of controlled substances without a prescription. 
No use or possession of checks/checkbooks/checking accounts. 
No use or possession of anyone else's personal identifying information/documents without their written consent. 
No contact with Mark Tucker.
No contact with known drug users or dealers unless in treatment setting or in confinement.  
No contact with Johnson Motors except to sign title of vehicle over to Johnson Motors. 
No contact with Osceola Auto Sales, Dallas Auto Sales or Centuria Stop gas station or Treasures of the Heart store.
No possession of firearms, BB guns or facsimile firearms. 
Cannot vote until civil rights restored, cannot hold elected office, other civil rights may be lost until restored. If not a US citizen, may face deportation or loss of other citizenship rights.

Must sign vehicle titles over of any of the fraudulently purchased vehicles to the dealership including signing the vehicle title over to Johnson Motors. Restitution to Johnson Motors is held open for 60 days to verify compliance that defendant has signed vehicle title over. 
Must follow all rules of probation.
Must complete any programming or treatment required by agent. 
Must provide a DNA sample.  Under Wisconsin Statute 165.76, you are required to provide a biological specimen to the Wisconsin Department of Justice for deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) testing.  If you fail to provide a DNA sample, you may be held in contempt and subject to sanctions or charged with a new crime.
Dunn County case 21CF307 is read-in for restitution and dismissed.

$490.00 restitution, plus a 10% surcharge of $49.00 and a 5% surcharge of $24.50, totaling $563.50 to be paid to the Clerk of Court's Office within 60 days or set up payment plan. 
$33.98 restitution, plus a 10% surcharge of $3.40 and a 5% surcharge of $1.70, totaling $39.08 to be paid to the Clerk of Court's Office within 60 days or set up payment plan. 
$56.57 restitution, plus a 10% surcharge of $5.66 and a 5% surcharge of $2.83, totaling $65.06 to be paid to the Clerk of Court's Office within 60 days or set up payment plan. 
Failure to pay may result in a tax intercept, license suspension, warrant and/or civil judgment subject to collection efforts.

Preliminary Hearing in 22CF28: Atty Chapman- waiver of PH. CT questions def re waiver of PH. CT accepts waiver of PH, def bound over. ADA has filed an information containing Pierce County charges for consolidation into 22CF28. Def has recv'd copy of information. Exh 1 recv'd- consolidation docs re Dunn County case 21CF307. Exh 2- consolidation docs re Pierce County cases 21CF122 & 21CF142. Atty Chapman- waives reading. NG pleas entered. 

Atty Chapman provided CT attachment to plea questionnaire containing resolution of multiple files. 
Felony warnings given, No firearms, loss of voting rights, holding public office, loss of citizenship rights etc.  Def requests to waive PSI. CT questions def re waiver of PSI. CT accepts waiver of PSI. 
21CF510 count 1 poss. meth- def- G plea.
21CF530 count 3 theft false representation- def- G plea.
21CF553 count 1 theft false representation- def- G plea.  
22CF28 count 1 theft false representation- def- G plea.
22CF28 count 8 unauthorized use of entity's identifying information (Pierce County 21CF122)- def- G plea.  
22CF28 count 6 forgery (Pierce county 21CF142)- def- G plea.
CT accepts pleas, adj G of each of those counts, judgment entered on each count today's date. All other counts and cases including Dunn County case 21CF307 is RI&D on state's motion without predj without costs. Sentencing arguments. Def makes statement. 

SENTENCE: 
May not possess or use firearms and, if considered a violent felony, no body armor. Cannot vote until civil rights restored, cannot hold elected office, other civil rights may be lost until restored. If not a US citizen, may face deportation or loss of other citizenship rights. $300.05 fine/costs on count 1 poss meth in 21CF510, $290.60 fine/costs on each remaining counts. $250 DNA surcharge and sample on each count.  Eligible for CIP and SA programs. 
21CF510 count 1 poss. meth: W/held sent 4 years probation on all cases.15 days credit if revoked. 
Probation conditions on all: AODA and comply. AS. No use or possession of controlled substances without a prescription. No contact w/Mark Tucker. No contact w/known drug users or dealers unless in treatment or confined. No use or possession of checks/checkbooks/checking accounts. Must sign over titles to any of the fraudulently purchased vehicles to the dealership including signing vehicle title over to Johnson Motors. 
Johnson Motors restitution is held open for 60 days for def to sign title over to Johnson Motors. 
No possession of firearms, BB guns, or facsimile firearms. 
Follow all rules of probation, complete any programming/treatment required by agent. 
Must report to probation. 
12 months stayed/banked jail on poss. meth charge. Subj to WR. Not subj to GT.

21CF553 count 1 theft false representation: W/held sent 4 years probation on all cases. $1,914.00 restitution to Dalles Auto Sales. 70 days credit if revoked.

Count 6:  $127.97 restitution plus the 10% surcharge.
Count 8:  $421.95 restitution plus the 10% surcharge.
Restitution amounts also subject to the additional 5% surcharge. All must be paid during probation term. FPT- judgment, subject to tax intercept, collection efforts.
